						               													<description>In Persian Carpet board game, each player plays as a carpet weaver artist, weaving carpets in their workshop and competing against other players to sell more carpets (matching the order cards they receive).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game plays in several rounds (depending on the number of players), and scores will reveal the winner at the end of the final round. Each round contains four phases: 1- Receiving money; 2- Buying yarns; 3- Weaving carpets; and 4- Selling carpets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of each round, each player receives money from the bank. Then they go to any of the two available markets to buy the yarns they need. Yarn colors with more demands are more expensive.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Any player who has all their needed yarns can start weaving the carpets by rolling dice to fulfill the order cards. Then, each player who has a completed carpet may sell it for money and victory points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends after a certain number of rounds, and the player with the highest score is the winner of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
